== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{12-13%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Beef and Beans ==

Meanwhile, trim the @Green Beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and green beans. Fry until the mince has browned and beans are tender, ~{6-7%mins}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

== Pak Choi and Garlic ==

Meanwhile, trim the @Pak Choi{1%unit}, then thinly slice widthways.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Sweet and Sticky Sauce ==

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, pak choi and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to the pan. Stir-fry, ~{1%min}.

Stir the @Hoisin Sauce{64%grams}, @Teriyaki Sauce{50%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} into the pan.

Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%mins}. Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== To Serve ==

Share the jasmine rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sweet and sticky beef.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!